Let's generate a few histograms for the full dataset¶
In [60]:
p1 <- ggplot(data, aes(longevity)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)
p2 <- ggplot(data, aes(basal_lvs)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)
p3 <- ggplot(data, aes(stem_lvs)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)
p4 <- ggplot(data, aes(total_lvs)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p5 <- ggplot(data, aes(status)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p6 <- ggplot(data, aes(rep_spd)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)
p7 <- ggplot(data, aes(flwr_num)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p8 <- ggplot(data, aes(frt_num)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p9 <- ggplot(data, aes(frt_hadena)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p10 <- ggplot(data, aes(reproduced)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p11 <- ggplot(data, aes(smut)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p12 <- ggplot(data, aes(num_smutted_fl)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p13 <- ggplot(data, aes(leaf_herb)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p14 <- ggplot(data, aes(gen_ENMY)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6)                 
p15 <- ggplot(data, aes(spec_ENMY)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6) 
                 
plot_grid(p1, p2,p3, p4, p5, p6, p7, p8, p9, p10, p11, p12, p13, p14, p15, label_size = 12)
